## Windows Host Execution

This container can execute commands on the Windows host machine. Use this when
a task requires Windows-specific tools, build systems, or programs that aren't
available inside the Linux container.

### How to use

Run commands on the host with `/opt/windows-exec/host-exec.sh`:

```bash
# Run a command via PowerShell (default)
/opt/windows-exec/host-exec.sh dotnet build MyProject.sln

# Run a command via cmd.exe
/opt/windows-exec/host-exec.sh --cmd msbuild /t:Build /p:Configuration=Release

# Set a working directory on the host
/opt/windows-exec/host-exec.sh --cwd "C:\Projects\MyApp" cargo build
```

### When to use

Use `host-exec.sh` when:

- A build requires a Windows-native tool (MSBuild, Visual Studio CLI, .NET SDK, etc.)
- You need to run a program that only has a Windows version
- The task references Windows paths or Windows-specific build steps
- An issue or PR mentions tools that aren't installed in this container but likely exist on the host

The host runs Windows and has its own set of installed tools. If a required tool
isn't available inside this container, try the host before reporting it as missing.
